Thank you to everyone that supported @westcoastelitetrackclub 1st Fundraising Event!! Rather you donated money or a bag, bought a ticket, reposted and shared, or simply prayed for a successful event we are truly grateful. We hosted a small intimate brunch, but it made such a huge impact. The ladies were able to fellowship over good food and drinks, bid on some beautiful designer bags, and a few of our WCE girls were able to Honor, meet, and speak with one of the greatest female track athletes of all time. However, as I reflect on all the many moments from yesterday there is one that sticks out to me the most and that is @mrs._tunai_anderson praying over the girls and their season. Everyone in the space leaned in to cover them, and to see all the girls with there heads bowed and so intensely into the prayer reminded me of why WE do this, why THEY do this, and that’s simply to glorify God! Thanks again for all your support and make sure to follow us along our 2023 Season!! It’s about to be BIG!!

***Long Post Alert***

I started my coaching journey over 10 years ago and to say it’s challenging would be an understatement. Coaching is about cultivating an environment for your athletes to thrive and be successful. Coaching is a skill. It’s mentorship, therapy, commitment, consistency, dedication, and more importantly it’s a GIFT. Although accolades, a thank you, and applause are always appreciated I don’t do any of this for anything in return. I understand I am on assignment, and I am grateful for the opportunity to serve. I have the ability to touch lives and I don’t take any of my influence for granted. 

I have been talked about, ridiculed, and judged by many, but I know I’m in alignment with God’s purpose for me, therefore I stay focused on that. If I was losing “they” wouldn’t have anything to say and that’s that on that.. LOL! What many coaches have yet to accomplish in a 20+ year career, I’ve done in half the time. As a former head high school track coach, and coaching my own youth team I’ve had numerous National Championship Qualifiers and Titles, over a handful of Meet Records, a National Record, State and US Leading times, over a dozen Top 25 US Ranked athletes, a CIF Championship, a State Title, guided many of my high school athletes to track college scholarships, and now a 2023 AAU Coach of the Year. What a Blessing! 

I have the opportunity to work with athletes who are immensely talented, and some who can’t walk and chew gum. LOL! Either way, I enjoy the process of seeing them all develop into greatness. I don’t evaluate my coaching abilities on the accomplishments of my athletes on the track, but rather the impact I have on them off the track, and how well they improve under my leadership. The 2023 Season was full of its challenges and the enemy was definitely busy, but in the words of the late Nipsey Hussle, “The Marathon Continues”!
2024 Season Loading… 

~ Coach Michel ✌🏾

That’s a wrap on the 2023 season filled with dedication, teamwork, and lots of trophies ! 🏆
